    longDescription: "Programme Duration\n4 Years Undergraduate Degree Programme\n\nEligibility Criteria\nStudents who have completed 10+2 (any stream) from a recognized board are eligible to apply. Students appearing for Class 12 examinations can also apply for admission.\n\nProgramme Fee\nTotal Programme Fee : ₹5,04,000.\nScholarship : Avail ₹ 50,000 Scholarship , Last Date to apply 31 st May 2026.\n\nBuild Your Career with a Leading Aviation Management College in Kolkata\nThe BBA in Aviation, Hospitality Services & Management at IAER Kolkata is a career-oriented programme designed for students who aspire to work in aviation, airlines, airports, hospitality, and tourism industries.\nIAER is widely recognized as one of the best aviation management colleges in Kolkata, offering a practical and industry-aligned curriculum. Students searching for a top aviation management college in Kolkata or a job-oriented aviation course after 12th will find this programme highly relevant for building a successful career.\nBy combining business management education with aviation operations and hospitality training, the programme ensures students are prepared for real-world industry roles.\n\nIndustry-Aligned Aviation & Hospitality Training\nAs a top BBA Aviation Operations college in Kolkata, IAER provides specialized training in key areas of aviation and service management.\nStudents gain knowledge and practical exposure in:\n Airport Operations & Management\n Airline Ground Handling & Passenger Services\n Aviation Safety & Service Standards\n Customer Experience Management\n Hospitality & Tourism Operations\nThis makes the programme ideal for students looking for aviation management courses after 12th or airport management courses in Kolkata with strong career prospects.\n\nCabin Crew Training & Personality Development\nIAER integrates professional grooming and communication training within the curriculum, making it a preferred choice for students aiming for airline careers. With structured modules aligned with a top cabin crew training college in Kolkata, students develop essential soft skills required in aviation and hospitality industries.\n\nTraining includes:\n Grooming & Professional Etiquette\n Communication & Soft Skills\n Airline Service Fundamentals\n Customer Handling & Guest Experience\n\nProgramme Highlights\n Industry-aligned aviation and hospitality curriculum\n Strong foundation in business and service management\n Internship opportunities with airlines, airports, and hotels\n Personality development and professional grooming\n Industry interaction and expert sessions\n Career-oriented training with placement support\n Pathway to MBA / PGDM in Aviation, Hospitality, or Tourism\n\nInternship Opportunities & Industry Exposure\nStudents gain real-world exposure through internships with leading organizations in aviation and hospitality sectors.\nInternship opportunities include:\n Airlines and aviation service providers\n Airports and ground handling companies\n Hotels and hospitality chains\n Travel and tourism organizations\n Event and service industry firms\nRoles include:\n Airport Operations Intern\n Airline Ground Staff Intern\n Cabin Services Intern\n Hotel Operations Intern\n Guest Relations Intern\n Travel & Tourism Intern\n Event & Hospitality Intern\nThese experiences help students build strong foundations for aviation and hospitality careers in India.\n\nCareer Opportunities & Aviation Jobs in Kolkata\nGraduates of this programme can explore a wide range of career opportunities across aviation, hospitality, and service industries. Many students aim for some of the best aviation jobs in Kolkata, while others explore opportunities across India and globally.\n\nAviation Careers:\n Airport Operations Executive\n Airline Customer Service Executive\n Ground Staff / Passenger Handling Executive\n Cabin Crew\n\nHospitality Careers:\n Hotel Operations Executive\n Front Office / Guest Relations Executive\n\nTravel & Tourism Careers:\n Travel Consultant\n Tourism Executive\n\nService & Management Roles:\n Event & Hospitality Coordinator\n Service Operations Supervisor\n Management Trainee\n\nGrowing Scope of Aviation & Hospitality Industry\nThe aviation and hospitality sectors are rapidly expanding due to increasing air travel, airport development, and tourism growth. This has created strong demand for graduates from top aviation management colleges in Kolkata and across India.\nCareer opportunities are available in:\n Domestic and international airlines\n Airport management companies\n Hotel and resort chains\n Cruise and luxury service industries\n Travel and tourism sector\n\nFrequently Asked Questions (FAQs)\n\nWhat is BBA in Aviation & Hospitality Management?\nIt is a professional undergraduate programme that combines business management with aviation operations, hospitality services, and customer experience training.\n\nWhich is the best aviation management college in Kolkata?\nIAER is considered one of the best aviation management colleges in Kolkata, offering industry-oriented training, internships, and placement support.\n\nIs BBA Aviation a good career option?\nYes, it provides strong career opportunities in airlines, airports, hospitality, tourism, and global service industries.\n\nDoes the programme include Internship in Airports?\nYes, Students get apply opportunity to pursue their internships in Selected Airports and Airlines.\n\nWhat are the best aviation jobs in Kolkata?\nPopular roles include airport operations executive, airline customer service executive, ground staff, and cabin crew.\n\nCan I join aviation after 12th?\nYes, students from any stream can apply for aviation and hospitality management programmes.\n\nEnquire Now – BBA Aviation Admission Open 2026\nLimited Seats Available\nScholarship Opportunities Available\nStart Your Career in Aviation & Hospitality Today\nEnquire Now | Book Your Seat | Get Free Counselling",
